recitals:
,
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EC) No 3119/93 of 8 November 1993 laying down special measures to encourage the processing of certain citrus fruits (1), and in particular Article 10 thereof,
Whereas Article 5 of Regulation (EC) No 3119/93 provides for an aid scheme for satsumas harvested in the Community and processed into segments; whereas the scheme comprises the grant of aid to citrus fruit producers' organizations for satsumas delivered  under contract to processors;
Whereas experience gained in the administration of the scheme implemented by Commission Regulation (EC) No 3338/93 (2) points to the need to change the rules applicable to aid applications from citrus fruit producers' organizations and to strengthen the  rules relating to the consequences for processors if they do not respect the minimum price to be paid to producers or to producers' organizations;
Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Fruit and Vegetables,
